## Fix Objects tab always querying bound Lakebase (not provisioner project)

Context: After a successful build, the Objects tab remained empty. Root cause:
`loadLakebaseObjects()` was forwarding `branch_path = lakebaseBranch.value` to
the backend. The Connection form pre-fills `lakebaseBranch` with the saved
provisioner branch (e.g., `projects/.../branches/...` for `ontobricks-test`).
The backend then connected to that provisioner project instead of the BOUND
Lakebase host (`ontobricks-demo2`) where `GraphDBFactory` had actually written
the graph data. Registry and graph share the same Lakebase host (PGHOST) but
use different databases.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/config/js/settings.js
   Remove branch_path from loadLakebaseObjects URL params; always rely on the
   bound Lakebase auth (empty branch_path triggers the correct fallback path).
   Remove branch_path from drop-object calls for the same reason.
   Remove dead branchSel/branchPath variables from the function scope.

Modified files:
- src/front/static/config/js/settings.js

Tests: n/a (integration suite requires live Databricks)

