## Support separate Lakebase project for graph DB (BranchLakebaseAuth)

Context: GraphDBFactory always used the bound Lakebase auth (PGHOST, the
registry project), ignoring the lakebase_project/lakebase_branch saved in
the Connection tab. When the user configures a different project for the
graph DB, writes would silently land in the registry's Lakebase instead.

The fix adds BranchLakebaseAuth — a drop-in auth alternative that resolves
the Postgres endpoint host and mints JWTs for a specific branch resource
path (projects/<proj>/branches/<branch>) via the Databricks Postgres API.
GraphDBFactory now instantiates BranchLakebaseAuth when lakebase_branch is
present in engine_config, falling back to the bound auth otherwise.
The Health probe was updated to match the same auth selection logic.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py
   Add BranchLakebaseAuth class: same interface as LakebaseAuth, resolves
   host/JWT from an explicit branch resource path, caches token ~55 min.

2. src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBFactory.py
   _create_lakebase: use BranchLakebaseAuth(branch_path, database_override)
   when engine_config.lakebase_branch is set; otherwise use get_lakebase_auth().

3. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   graph_engine_lakebase_health_result: mirror the same auth selection so
   the Health panel connects to the same host as the build engine.

Modified files:
- src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py
- src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBFactory.py
- src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py

Tests: n/a (integration suite requires live Databricks)

