## Fix "database does not exist" race in LakebaseGraphProvisioner

Context: "Create Graph DB" failed with "database ontobricks_graph_db does not
exist". The control-plane API reported the DB as created (making _database_exists
return True) before Postgres actually accepted connections to it. The schema
creation step then immediately tried to connect and got the error.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/provisioner.py
   _step_create_database: add Phase 2 reachability poll after Phase 1 API
   listing check. New _wait_for_db_reachable helper retries a lightweight
   psycopg connect up to 15 times (5s apart, ~75s) until the database accepts
   connections, or warns and proceeds if the timeout is exceeded.

Modified files:
- src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/provisioner.py

Tests: n/a (integration suite requires live Databricks)

