## Full graph/registry Lakebase separation audit — fix remaining sites

Context: Comprehensive audit revealed that graph DB operations (objects listing,
drop, schema discovery, health probe) still connected to the bound registry
Lakebase instead of the separately-configured graph Lakebase project. This
contradicts the core architecture: registry and graph DB are totally separate
Lakebase instances. Four sites were broken; all now use the same auth selection
as GraphDBFactory (BranchLakebaseAuth when lakebase_branch is configured).

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   Add _graph_engine_auth() static helper: resolves correct Lakebase auth
   (BranchLakebaseAuth or bound) + effective database from saved config,
   with form params taking priority. Single source of truth for all graph
   operations in SettingsService.

2. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   graph_engine_lakebase_objects_result: replace manual bound-auth fallback
   with _graph_engine_auth(); removes stale comment about bound host.

3. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   graph_engine_lakebase_drop_object_result: same — use _graph_engine_auth();
   also fixes missing database fallback (was only applied when database param
   truthy, now correctly resolved from saved config).

4. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   graph_engine_lakebase_pg_schemas_result: replace BranchLakebaseAuth(branch_path)
   with _graph_engine_auth() so saved lakebase_branch is used when branch_path
   form param is empty.

5. src/shared/fastapi/health.py
   _check_graphdb_lakebase: stop using LakebaseRegistryStore (registry pool).
   Now selects BranchLakebaseAuth vs bound auth from engine_cfg.lakebase_branch,
   then opens a direct psycopg connection on the graph host.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
- src/shared/fastapi/health.py

Tests: n/a (integration suite requires live Databricks)

