## Fix BranchLakebaseAuth missing branch_name — managed_synced mode broken

Context: After switching to BranchLakebaseAuth for graph operations, builds
in managed_synced mode failed with "managed_synced mode active but no
SyncedTableManager was wired". Root cause: BranchLakebaseAuth was missing
the branch_name property. GraphDBFactory._build_synced_manager called
auth.branch_name, got AttributeError, fell back silently... but the
LakebaseFlatStore was somehow still created in managed_synced state without
a manager.

Fix: add branch_name and annotate instance_name on BranchLakebaseAuth.
The branch resource path "projects/<proj>/branches/<branch>" provides both:
instance_name = parts[1] (project name), branch_name = parts[-1] (branch name).
SyncedTableManager can now be built correctly for graph projects.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py
   BranchLakebaseAuth: add branch_name property (last path segment),
   annotate instance_name docstring for clarity.

Modified files:
- src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py

Tests: n/a (integration suite requires live Databricks)

