## Lakebase Permissions tab — grant Postgres superuser from the UI

**Context**: After deploying the automated superuser grant in the provisioner, users found it still
didn't work reliably (SCIM lookup unreliable when running as SP). The new Permissions tab gives admins
a direct UI to grant `DATABRICKS_SUPERUSER` to any user on demand, without re-running the provisioner.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py`
   - Added `branch_path` property to `LakebaseAuth`: returns `projects/<inst>/branches/<branch>`
     (triggers endpoint resolution on first call, same cost as `.host`).
   - Added `branch_path` property to `BranchLakebaseAuth`: returns `self._branch_path` directly.

2. `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`
   - `graph_engine_lakebase_pg_roles_result(session_mgr, settings)`: lists all Postgres roles on
     the configured graph Lakebase branch via `GET /api/2.0/postgres/{branch_path}/roles`; overlays
     app-user principals to produce a combined roles + app_users response.
   - `graph_engine_lakebase_grant_superuser_result(user_email, session_mgr, settings)`: idempotent
     grant — creates `LAKEBASE_OAUTH_V1` Postgres role if absent, then PATCHes to add
     `DATABRICKS_SUPERUSER` membership. Mirrors provisioner logic, reusable outside the provision flow.

3. `src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`
   - `GET /settings/graph-engine/lakebase-pg-roles` (admin only): delegates to service above.
   - `POST /settings/graph-engine/lakebase-grant-superuser` (admin only): body `{user_email}`.

4. `src/front/templates/settings.html`
   - Added "Permissions" tab (nav item + pane) between Objects and Advanced in the Lakebase section.
   - Pane: email input + Grant button, Refresh button, status banner, two tables
     (application users with role/superuser status, all Postgres roles).

5. `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`
   - `loadLakebasePermissions()`: fetches roles + app users, renders both tables with status badges
     and per-row Grant buttons (disabled when already superuser).
   - `grantSuperuser(email)`: POSTs to grant endpoint, shows inline progress/success/error, refreshes
     the table on success.
   - `escHtml()`: local HTML-escaping helper for safe innerHTML rendering.

