## Permissions tab — fix Grant button scope + replace text input with user dropdown

**Context**: The Grant button did nothing because `grantSuperuser` and `loadLakebasePermissions`
were defined inside the `DOMContentLoaded` closure but called via `onclick=` string attributes
which look up names in the global scope. Also the text input was replaced with a proper dropdown
populated from application users (CAN USE + CAN MANAGE) to make granting more ergonomic.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/templates/settings.html`
   - Removed `onclick=` from the Permissions tab `<button>` (was ignored anyway by Bootstrap tabs).
   - Replaced the free-form email `<input>` with a `<select id="lkPermUserSelect">` dropdown.
   - Added `id="btnLkPermGrant"` and `id="btnLkPermRefresh"` on action buttons (no inline JS).
   - Simplified table: single merged table (app users + orphan Postgres roles) replacing the two
     separate tables.

2. `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`
   - `loadLakebasePermissions()`: no more `onclick=` in generated HTML — row Grant buttons use
     `btn.dataset.email` + `btn.addEventListener('click', ...)`.
   - Dropdown is populated from the merged `allRows` list (app_users first, then any Postgres roles
     not already in app_users). Previous selection is preserved across refreshes.
   - `_lkPermGrantEmail(email)`: renamed internal helper (not global), handles the fetch + banner.
   - IIFE at the bottom wires `shown.bs.tab` → first load, `btnLkPermGrant` click → grant selected
     user, `btnLkPermRefresh` click → reload — all via `addEventListener`, no global pollution.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/templates/settings.html`
- `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`

**Test result**: 2385 passed, 1 pre-existing skip. Deployed: `make deploy`.
